records.addlTxt:
10:53 AM Defendant Joshua S Campbell in court.  Attorney Shunette Torna Campbell in court for Joshua S Campbell.  Prosecuting attorney Rose Marie Yanke in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Attorney Campbell Hunter is requesting this matter be reset. Court grants and bond is continued. Attorney Campbell Hunter requests to be court appointed on this issue and his family case as well. Court grants.
Final pre-trial scheduled for January 13, 2023 at 11:00 am.
Letter from the Family Center regarding the status of visitation
Letter from DA's Office w/ copy of a letter from Family Center to Victim

2:00 PM Prosecuting attorney Rose Marie Yanke in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Joshua S Campbell in court.  Attorney Shunette Torna Campbell in court for Joshua S Campbell. 
Officer Burger is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being an Officer with the City of Wisconsin Rapids. Testifies to his training and education. Testifies to being dispatched to an incident that occurred between BTS and the defendant. Witness identifies the defendant in court, court recognizes. Testifies to the victim stating the sexual assault occurred at her apartment. Testifies to the statement made by victim regarding what happened. Testifies to the victim telling the defendant no. Testifies to the victim stating this has happened in the past with the defendant. Testifies to his conversation with the defendant and the defendant denying the allegations. 

Attorney Campbell cross examines the witness. Witness testifies to the victim going to see a SANE nurse the following day. Testifies to taking the defendant into custody after speaking with him. Testifies to evidence that was collected. 
Attorney Campbell makes an argument regarding this being a felony charge.

Court finds probable cause to believe a felony was committed and the defendant committed it.

Bond is continued.

Attorney Campbell informs the court the defendant has set completed intake w/ the Family Center and the mother isn't complying.
Final pre-trial scheduled for October 21, 2022 at 11:00 am.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on July 13, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
No contact with alleged victim (BTS) or residence. Arrangements for child visitation through the Family Center and supervised visits must take place at the Family Center. $10,000
Court appoints Attorney Shunette Campbell Hunter as counsel - Defendant must pay $50.00 per month toward attorney fees commencing July 1, 2022
